gomodel:SYNGO_534  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: Fig. 1a,c Nav1.8 co-localize with the presynaptic proteins synaptophysin and bassoon\nLiteral\n\"Nav1.8 co-localize with the presynaptic proteins synaptophysin and bassoon in axonal boutons of DRG neurons.\"\n\n15/5/2017 Pim\n- Authors state:\n\"We also found that the majority of Nav1.8- and Nav1.9-positive boutons were associated with the postsynaptic density protein PSD95 (Fig. 1E, F ...\"\n\"Overall, these data indicate that Nav1.8 and Nav1.9 are presynaptically expressed in a large proportion of DRG neurons. \"\n\n- 'Integral ...' term derived from TM domains of Nav1.8.. Experimental description: Experiment of neuronal colture staining are made in rat.\nLiteral from M&M\n\"DRG/SC co-cultures were prepared as previously described (Medvedeva et al., 2008). \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_534" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

